<TITLE> 2 'muggers' lynched in port city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  Two alleged muggers were lynched and one was injured as they were trying to run away after robbing a rickshaw rider in Pahartali area in the city on Friday, police said. The dead were identified as Khokon, 21, and Jahid, 20, who died on the way to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. The injured, identified as Shahin, 20, was undergoing treatment in CMCH. He was also reportedly in critical condition. Witnesses said three muggers riding a motorcycle tried to get away with the purse from a woman, Mita, who gave only one name, at around 6:30pm. Mita and her husband were taking a rickshaw ride. They instantly cried out for help and people nearby caught the muggers and beat them up, according to the witnesses. Police went to the scene and took the wounded to the hospital. Two of them died on the way, Iltut Mish, assistant police commissioner of Pahartali Zone, told bdnews24.com. The robbed valuables were recovered, he said. A case was being filed when Mish spoke to bdnews24.com. bd
